content: This is the most comprehensive machining app I've used so far. Would be nice to have the Imperial tapping charts split into BSW, BA, UNC, UNF ect. The FSWizard could also do with options for BSW, BA, BSP and NPT taps. Thanks for making an excellent app, if you could add in an ISO bearing fit chart and Key-way charts I'd be able to throw out my engineers handbook.
replyContent:
Thank you for the suggestions.
Expansion of thread charts is on my things to do list.

content: Speed and feed provided by this app may seem aggressive at first but once you learn to trust it you will see that its right every time. Sure it's a bit pricey but so were your fancy digital mics. Keep up the great work Zero_Divide, your work here is genius.
I use it every day. It's time best app on my phone.
Been a job shop/cnc machinist for 25 years. This app is one of my best tools. If you do not use this app, you are wasting valuable time.

The only issue I found were some glaring spelling mistakes. This app is, hands down, the best of its kind on the market! UPDATE:  I just found a major bug with tapping w/ cobalt taps w/ a coating. RPM is WAY too high when calculating for any material. The real difference between HSS and Cobalt is less than 10%. 9000+ RPM in 6061??? The cutting speeds given for tapping can not be trusted for any material. Great app for everything else. Tapping needs work.
replyContent: Going to make one final push and finally eradicate misspells. UPDATE: this concern was voiced before and i have looked into it. Everything is fine. For small taps you will get sometimes very high RPM (especially in aluminum) and you need to use RPM limit. shoot me an email for more info.

content: Good reference.  In the end you need to use the tool manufacturer's recommendations.
replyContent:
Hi,
The calculator is designed to give you safe numbers that will work in MOST cases.

Setting 150% feed and 150% speed override will give you numbers close to what most tool manufacturers will suggest in their tables.

content: This app is amazing! Only one I found that allows you to select the material that you are working on rather than inputting numbers from a separate table. I am a student machinist and I do not know things like the ipt for different materials by heart so this app is perfect. The way the UI is setup allows for quick recalculation for different depths of cut. I definitely recommend.  The one feature that would be great would be an option for extended tool life rather than the absolute fastest rpm and table feed
replyContent:
Hi, Thanks for a great review!
Good idea. Normally you can control tool life by changing cutting speed.
Say a 25% reduction in cutting speed will very often yield 2 times increase in tool life.
I will add several buttons in "Overrides" tab that will preset cutting speed for better life or better productivity
